text: on Wednesday the fifth day of its
military strike into Gaza Israel
rejected it calls for a 48-hour
ceasefire its planes continued to pound
Hamas especially tunnels it says they're
used to smuggle weapons into Gaza Hamas
meantime fired off some 30 or 40 rockets
going deeper into Israeli territory than
ever before Wednesday marked the kind of
transition in this conflict there was
less actual fighting but Israel is under
increasing international pressure to
minimize the impact on civilians the UN
says that so far more than 60 women and
children have been killed hospitals and
Gaza are running out of supplies and
food is running short but Israel does
not want to let up on Hamas militarily
so it seems to be following a
three-pronged strategy it hopes will
allow it to do everything first it is
continuing air strikes second it's
exploring ways even in the fighting to
get more food and medical supplies into
Gaza the third prong is aimed at calming
international fears it says it will
engage in talks started by the French to
try to reimpose a longer-term ceasefire
with Hamas
